column2: These hourly factors are used to convert predicted site energy use to long run marginal greenhouse gas emissions.
These hourly factors must be used with a computer program approved for demonstrating compliance with the 2025 Energy Code by the California Energy Commission.
These hourly factors are formatted to the 2009 calendar year, where January 3rd & 4th are the first weekend of the year.
These hourly factors assume a 30-year period of analysis.
